annotation.TEXT: "BOMB" fireworks FTW!
Okay, let me just grab that missile pickup...

Now, it doesn't look like Gemini Man can reach the pipe from above, but can he double jump to it from the left? Yes he can! And due to the weird pipe-entering hit detection in Crossover, he can enter it too!

What this power up does is temporarily make me act like I'm swimming in midair. (Kind of reminds me of a particular Game Genie code I liked to use on SMB3 back in the day... I think it was "YEUXKGAA".)
Nothing in the pipe either, so whatever. (Aww, no bonus room in this castle?)
However, according to the Wiki, the wing power up will show up again in 4-1. Maybe it'll be much more useful there.
Alright, it's boss time! And, just like last time, I'm gonna plaster Bowser with a bunch of missiles!
SMBS demo count: 4
Now, I expect 3-3 to have a power up, so I'll pick Gemini Man here, in the hopes that I can get a Gemini Laser power up (if it exists in Crossover). I'll go with the Wily Wars Gemini Man this time.
Oh, and I can get this 1-up again to replace that lost life.
That appears to be the goal up ahead. Now, let's see if I can time this right...
Whoa, there's a hidden block.
Votes for Google to change the comments back: At least 224,655.
So, are we going underground again?
Ooh, a pipe. Alright, anything is better than the underwater area.

Huh. I thought Samus's bombs could defeat armored foes like Buzzies. (However, I checked this later, and her bombs don't work on Buzzies. But, missiles do, and they work on those "barrels" as well, so if I had tried the missiles, I would've been fine. D'oh!)

Alright, now the voting results are shown above, and the alt. skin votes included 2 for Toad (Mario), 1 for Gemini Man (Bass) in a level that has a power up, and 1 for Toad Man (which isn't a skin in this game right now, unfortunately).
Now I'm going to jump around randomly in case there's something hidden around here that I might find.
You are freaking kidding me. I managed to screw it up the exact same way again anyway!
Wow, what's with Gemini Man often getting Castlevania themes? Must just be random luck.
Oh, and I will not be breaking any of the balance lifts, because of the risk of possibly being unable to jump away. (Well, actually, Gemini Man has a double jump, making it less risky, but whatever.)
It kind of feels like the wing power up is wasted here though, since there's very little need to swim through the air in this place.
Oh, and there's the goal.
I'm not going to waste time with the hammer either this time.
Yeah, there'd better be hidden blocks here to help me make this jump!
3-1 votes: 5
Alright, now that I got the 1-up, I'm outta here.
SMBS demo count: 2

Well, since this is a mushroom this time, I should be able to claim it. It's a bummer that I couldn't get that screw attack last time, though... (If I had known about that hidden block in the way beforehand, I would've tried to morph ball jump through it.)
Well, it might be a little useful here, but these jumps really don't look all that hard...
Being able to morph ball in midair is quite useful.
There it is-- The hammer! Now, it works just like in Donkey Kong. Too bad it doesn't have its signature music to go with it here...
Aww, the hammer wore off already, and I can't shoot these things (which apparently act like DK's barrels).
Fortunately, midpoint put me right near the power up and the pipe, so I can do all that again. Too bad I lost my Pharaoh Shot...
I think I overdid it on the missiles a bit there...
Okay, I think what happened was, I fell off the platform just before I hit the jump button, wasting my double jump right there, which doomed me.
Yeah, I'm betting there's a power up in that row of ? blocks, so I'm going to go back and hit them all.
I'll go with... the NES Toad this time.
Or, the horizontal pipe could have me dropping from the sky into a different overworld area. Okay...
Whoa, almost forgot about his double jump for a split-second there, but I'm good. (That would've been a silly death!)
Oy, this is getting stupid. Okay, I'm just going to get the power up behind me here and then make a beeline for the goal, since you guys probably don't want to see me repeat that bonus room again.
Heck, yeah! Got the AWESOME PHARAOH SHOT! ...Eh, I don't know if that deserves all caps like AWESOME SPREAD GUN...
Umm... That was definitely not the right timing, and I just pulled a raocow.

What? Another power up already? There were really two power ups right next to each other here? Also, apparently, you get the upgrades after Hyper in a random order. I just happened to get them in the usual Blaster Master order last time.
Well, the jump was makeable anyway. However, the left-most coins here appear to be unreachable without falling, unless I was using a character that could double jump or hover.
There seems to be a slight audio desync here. Is it because I paused the video recording? But, I had paused the recording once in an earlier episode, and I don't think that caused a desync...
Oh, and now I come out of this pipe near the start that I pointed out before.
Umm... But, is that it? Just the one hidden coin block and nothing else?
The SMB2 graphics here keep making me want to try and lift up the red patches of grass on the ground.
Alright, now I do see that differently-styled block up there, but I'm not going to hit it quite yet. I want to see what's to the right first.
Oh, and I'll want to be on the lookout for another unique item here.
Whoa, stay away from me, Blooper.
Yep, it's a 1-up. Now to walk to the right with it and wait for it to fall to me.
To be continued...
SMBS demo count: 3
Ooh, a Screw Attack! Aww... But I can't reach it... Maybe I can come back to it later from the right? We'll see.
Oh, and there's the goal. Wow, I could've skipped practically the whole level if I wanted, but then we wouldn't have seen the wing power up here!
Yeah, something tells me that block back there contains a 1-up, so let's go hit it and see.
D'oh! That stupid hidden block prevents me from going back for the Screw Attack!
Good thing I'm using a character that can actually "swim", and not just merely get an increased jump height! (Yeah, I totally didn't intentionally pick Sophia III here for this reason.)
Okay, there's that pipe I entered earlier, so back to the right I go.
What? I can't bomb those things either?! NOOOOO!!!!!
Hello, and welcome back to SMB Crossover! Now, UltraLeet31337 informed me that I missed a hidden 1-up in 2-2, so I'm back here to show that off.
Hyper gun upgrade acquired.

Anything up here? Doesn't look like it. That would've been a good place to hide something that you'd need the wing power up to reach. Oh, and it looks like the wing power up wore off without warning. I'm glad I didn't fall into a pit suddenly because of that!
Aww... It picked Samus? But I used Samus in the last castle... Oh, well...
Alright, now nobody voted for this next choice, but I've decided to take the Tetris-mobile out for a spin, just to give Sophia III a chance to be powered up for later, just in case.
...Except perhaps a flying cheepo area. GAAAMMMEEE!!!
I'm guessing the horizontal pipe is meant to bring me to this pipe up here. Let's check that out.
Yes, there we go! I missed the 6 fireworks, but I'm just happy to make the jump this time!
Umm... Is there no invisible block or anything here to help me make this jump?
No, we're underwater again. Already? And in the first level of a world? (Well, SMB3 did that, but SMB3's world 3 was water themed anyway, and this game is based off of SMB1...)
Huh. Apparently you can wall climb up a horizontal pipe instead of entering it if you're holding up as you hit it.
Hi!
Alright, now let's go with Random for 3-4 and hope for something good...
And, there it is-- The wing power up!
And, hopefully, I won't have any more mishaps like I did in this episode... Oh, and happy Friday the 13th, everyone!
Alright, so it's split between Toad and Random, and the votes favored 3-1 for both of them... I think I'll go with Toad for 3-1, and choose Random later.
Ooh, homing missiles.
I'm just getting a quick feel for the timing of my jumps and walking off ledges here. I don't want to repeat the same mistake in front of the flagpole again.
Oh, and from what I read on the Wiki earlier, there should be a Special-exclusive item in this level that I'll want to find.
There was also 1 vote to end the 3-1 meme (Never!!!), and 2 votes for YouTube's mobile app to display annotations.
Now, can I avoid stupidly falling to my death a third time here?
Ooh, Snake Man's theme! Alright, now since I'm not hurting for time yet, I think I'll check out what this bonus room had skipped to the left.
Well, let's try this again, with less getting crushed this time...
Although, I'm wondering if I should've gone with one of the other Sophia III skins... Oh, well.
Oh, hidden blocks! (Which I probably would've found no matter what, due to the presence of the ? block in the ceiling.)
Well, that hidden coin block seems rather arbitrary then.

And, there it is. Also, the pattern embedded in the wall on the far right of this room says "I.S" for some reason. Well, whatever. Now, nothing I do here will affect my current save, which I'm going to load up in just a moment here.
Score! (No number showed, but I certainly did get 5000 from the flag.)
I can roll down here, and it seems like a way to avoid Bowser's flames, but there's no goodies down here.
Alright, so which characters should I use for world 4? Place your votes now, and try to pick characters/skins that I haven't used yet, or at least haven't used in the SMB Special maps yet.
Yep, there's a power up. Be sure to catch it!
Huh. There's a pipe down there. I'll take a closer look at that in a moment. First, let's blast a duder and get a power up.
Actually, I think the flying cheepos (Trouters in this case) have stopped. Also, I can easily take the lower route here since I'm small.
